Find Longest Word in String | Find the longest word in a given sentence. 


class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "The quick brown fox jumps";
        System.out.println("Longest word in string: "+ longestWord(str));
    }
    public static String longestWord(String str){
        String longest = "";
        String[] words = str.split("\\s+");                      // split the string
        for(String word : words){
            if(word.length() >= longest.length()){
                longest = word;
            }
        }
        return longest;
    }
}

output:
Longest word in string: jumps


Summary:
To get the first longest word (like quick), use:
if (word.length() > longest.length())

To get the last one (like jumps), use:
if (word.length() >= longest.length())
